  "body": "I had a geth node of version 1.9.25 run in light mode synced up to the block #12535738. Then upgraded it to 1.10.3 and re-run on May, 30th. Since then geth stuck with the message:\r\n`Rewinding chain to upgrade configuration err=\"mismatching Berlin fork block in database (have <nil>, want 12244000, rewindto 12243999)\"`\r\n\r\n1 week passed, no new messages have been printed. Only ~/.ethereum/geth/les.client/000001.log slowly grows by ~0.5MB per day.\r\n\r\nAre this message and the delay expected behavior? When sould I expect the end of chain rewind?\r\n\r\nOS: Linux\r\ngeth: 1.10.3\r\ngo: 1.16.4\r\ndisk: HDD Toshiba DT01ACA200\r\ncommand line: `geth --syncmode=light --cache=512`\r\n",
